Want to place a custom order for multiple 
items?

No problem, you can use this simple one-click ordering process below. 
Just select a Buy Now button below with the shipping applicable to the 
items you are ordering, tell us what parts you want and how much they 
cost and your payment/shipping information and that is all that is 
needed.


    All 4Crawler Offroad products are FOB 
    seller/origin. 
    
    Add up the cost of each item you want included in your order (excluding 
    postage): 
    

        Typical kit contents and totals are listed in the tables on the pages 
        above 
        
        Add 9.0% sales tax for shipments to a California address:

Automaticaaly added if using the Buy Now buttons below
If you live outside of California, no sales tax applies 


        For US addresses, add $7.00 for small items that fit in an envelope or 
        $15.00 for uninsured or $18.00 for insured
         Priority Mail shipping, for a total 
        

            Or use one of the "Buy Now" buttons below for pre-computed 
            shipping. 
            
            3 day typical Priority Mail delivery time 
        

International shipping
         options, also supply a local phone number for customs paperwork 


            US Mail shipping to Canada/Mexico of US$45.00 for all the above kits 
            
            US Priority Mail shipping to Europe/Central and South Americaof 
            US$67.00 for most items 
            
            US Priority Mail shipping to Asia/Australia/New Zealand of US$75.00 for 
            most items 
            
            For total weight up to 20 pounds 
            
            Typical shipping time is 6-10 days 
            
            20 lb. weight limit on the above international shipments. 
            

                For smaller items, under 4 lbs. and that will fit in a letter size flat 
                rate envelope, international postage runs US$33.00. 
                
                While many items fit this 4 lb. weight limitation, they generally can't 
                be combined as that will push the weight over the limit. Examples are 
                ball joint spacers (3 lbs.), Diff Drop Kit (2.5 lbs.), Panhard Drop 
                Brkt. (3 lbs.), etc. So no way to combine those sorts of parts into the 
                flat rate envelope, only option is the 20 lb. limit flat rate box, 
                

                    Note that the flat rate box shipping option does offer better package 
                    tracking than the envelope, as 
                    noted. So if that is a consideration, you might 
                    want to opt for the flat rate box shipping option. 
                    
                    One other consideration on shipping multiple items is for customs/duty 
                    fees at the destination country. If you have two packages worth say 
                    US$50/ea. the customs/duty fees may be much less than for one package 
                    with a US$100 value. 
                


Shipping 
            insurance available by special request.

Currency conversion



    Specify the vehicle details if applicable 
    
Or order all the items separately and we'll be happy to combine 
    the shipping (if desired) and ship in one package and refund 
    any excess postage. 
    

        May or may not be possible in all cases due to size and/or weight 
        limitations, but we'll do our best. 
    

    Shipping options below do not apply to Rock SliderZ kit orders as they 
    have their own shipping options 
    
Questions? 


And you can always order each item separately and then let us 
know if you want them combined into one shipment, if possible 
and we'll do that and refund any excess postage. But you need to tell 
us since some customers like to have things shipped separately as there 
are a few advantages. For example if you order 3 items, if we ship 
together we'll need to wait until all 3 items are ready to ship before 
we can send anything. Also, for international customers, if you had 4 
orders for $50/ea. and shipped them separately, there may be no customs 
fees due since the value is below the minimum assessment value, while a 
single order of $200 might be assessed taxes and fees. So please let us 
know your preferences for shipping multiple item orders.

Ordering/payment options below:


